<subSubSection id="70B417B5FFC4FFC916D7FA65FE635F15" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="3811443EFFC4FFC916D7FA65FE635F15" blockId="28.[151,1437,1476,2043]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC916D7FA65FE035CA5" bold="true" box="[151,465,1476,1502]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Material (
<specimenCount id="2EA88FB7FFC4FFC91755FA65FE165CA5" box="[277,452,1476,1502]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
):
</emphasis>
Four adult specimens (MHNCUP/REP 327–330, formerly UP-MHNFCP-017405, 017424, 017406 and 017425 respectively; 
<figureCitation id="A09558BBFFC4FFC91435FA49FD055F78" box="[629,727,1512,1539]" captionStart="FIGURE S" captionStartId="70.[151,250,1076,1100]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,164,1051]" captionTargetId="figure-33@70.[151,1435,161,1053]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURE S57. Specimen of Causus resimus (MHNCUP/REP 327), from unknown locality. Photo by Bruna Santos." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454097/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. S57</figureCitation>
), collected from unknown locality, date unknown; 
<specimenCount id="2EA88FB7FFC4FFC91352FA48FA4E5F79" box="[1298,1436,1512,1539]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="juvenile">one juvenile</specimenCount>
specimen (MHNCUP/REP 331, formerly UP-MHNFCP-095050), collected from unknown locality, date unknown; 
<materialsCitation id="88C64E63FFC4FFC916D7F990FE7F5F15" collectorName="S. Tome" country="Sao Tome and Principe" location="Principe" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-adult="1">
<specimenCount id="2EA88FB7FFC4FFC916D7F990FED25F31" box="[151,256,1584,1611]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="adult">one adult</specimenCount>
specimen (MHNCUP/REP 336, formerly UP-MHNFCP-017426), collected from 
<collectorName id="955B21E8FFC4FFC912E7F991FAD75F31" box="[1191,1285,1584,1610]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. Tomé</collectorName>
and 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFC4FFC9137FF991FA4E5F31" box="[1343,1436,1584,1610]" name="Sao Tome and Principe" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Príncipe</collectingCountry>
(in error), date unknown
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="70B417B5FFC4FFC91687F9D9FC8C5E80" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3811443EFFC4FFC91687F9D9FC8C5E80" blockId="28.[151,1437,1476,2043]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC91687F9D9FE805FE9" bold="true" box="[199,338,1656,1682]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC4FFC91715F9D9FDD35FE9" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[341,513,1656,1682]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Causus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="resimus">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC91715F9D9FDD35FE9" box="[341,513,1656,1682]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Causus resimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be found throughout sub-SaharanAfrica, with a seemingly disjointed distribution (see 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC9168CF93CFE7D5FCD" author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[204,431,1692,1719]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC91776F93CFEA25FCD" box="[310,368,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
for more detail). The species is also known from the coastal savannas and woodlands of western 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFC4FFC916B4F961FE945FA1" box="[244,326,1728,1754]" name="Angola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Angola</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC91716F961FDEC5FA1" author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[342,574,1728,1754]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC91781F960FE285FA1" box="[449,506,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC91411F961FD2E5FA1" author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[593,764,1728,1754]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="111 - 117" refId="ref37152" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1904) Reptis e amphibios de Angola da regiao ao norte do Quanza (Colleccao Newton 1903). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (25), 111 - 117." type="journal article" year="1904">Ferreira (1904)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<specimenCount id="2EA88FB7FFC4FFC91501F961FC6B5FA1" box="[833,953,1728,1754]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="adult">three adult</specimenCount>
specimens from “Cazengo”, “Caculo” and “Cabicula”, possibly matching extant specimens MHNCUP/REP 327–330. Additionally, 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC9123EF945FAFA5F84" author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[1150,1320,1764,1791]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref37198" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1906) Algumas especies novas ou pouco conhecidas de amphibios e reptis de Angola (Coleccao Newton - 1903 - 1904). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (26), 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="1906">Ferreira (1906)</bibRefCitation>
published an adult of 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC91758F8A9FDC75E59" box="[280,533,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
“ 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC4FFC91762F8A9FDD85E59" baseAuthorityName="Lichtenstein" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[290,522,1800,1826]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Causus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rhombeatus">Causus rhombeatus</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
from “Golungo Alto” that we were unable to locate. The Angolan population of 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC4FFC916D7F88DFEDD5E3D" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[151,271,1836,1862]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Causus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="resimus">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC916D7F88DFEDD5E3D" box="[151,271,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. resimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very isolated from its counterparts in East Africa, suggesting that it might be different. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC916D7F8F1FEEC5E11" author="Branch, W. R." box="[151,318,1872,1898]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="159" refId="ref34681" refString="Branch, W. R. (2018) Snakes of Angola: An annotated checklist. Amphibian &amp; Reptile Conservation, General Section, 12 (2), e 159, 41 - 82." type="journal article" year="2018">Branch (2018)</bibRefCitation>
, the molecular phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC4FFC914CFF8F1FD335E11" authorityName="Wagler" authorityYear="1830" box="[655,737,1872,1898]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Causus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC914CFF8F1FD335E11" box="[655,737,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Causus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is being addressed by Tolley 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC91279F8F0FBA15E11" box="[1081,1139,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
(in prep) and preliminary results indicate cryptic diversity within 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC91412F8D5FD025EF5" box="[594,720,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC4FFC91412F8D5FD1E5EF5" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[594,716,1908,1934]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Causus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="resimus">C. resimus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
thus supporting the hypothesis of the Angolan population being distinct. In that case, two different names have been proposed to refer to the species – 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC4FFC9120BF839FABC5EC9" authority="Stejneger, 1893" authorityName="Stejneger" authorityYear="1893" box="[1099,1390,1944,1970]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Causus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nasalis">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC9120BF839FB685EC9" box="[1099,1210,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. nasalis</emphasis>
Stejneger, 1893
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC4FFC916D7F81DFD885EAC" authority="Bocage, 1895" authorityName="Bocage" authorityYear="1895" box="[151,602,1980,2007]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Causus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" species="resimus" variety="angolensis">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC916D7F81DFEDF5EAD" box="[151,269,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. resimus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC91703F81DFE695EAD" box="[323,443,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">angolensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC91780F81CFD885EAC" author="Bocage, J. V. B." box="[448,602,1980,2007]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref34376" refString="Bocage, J. V. B. (1895) Herpetologie d'Angola et du Congo. Ministerio da Marinha e das Colonias, Lisboa, 203 pp., 20 pls." type="book" year="1895">Bocage, 1895</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC91427F81DFD2F5EAD" author="Branch, W. R." box="[615,765,1980,2006]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="159" refId="ref34681" refString="Branch, W. R. (2018) Snakes of Angola: An annotated checklist. Amphibian &amp; Reptile Conservation, General Section, 12 (2), e 159, 41 - 82." type="journal article" year="2018">Branch 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Although 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC4FFC9153DF81DFC3E5EAD" authorityName="Stejneger" authorityYear="1893" box="[893,1004,1980,2006]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Causus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nasalis">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC9153DF81DFC3E5EAD" box="[893,1004,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. nasalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has seniority, further research needs to be conducted to infer which would be the correct 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC91483F840FCDC5E81" box="[707,782,2017,2042]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">nomen</emphasis>
to use.
</paragraph>
